<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Cresson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-22"><hi rend="italic">April 22,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have been informed by minister for foreign affairs of Peru that
                            Ecuadorian answer proposing mutual excuses is not at all satisfactory to
                            Peru and their proposals to resume direct negotiations inadmissible.
                            Warlike preparations continue methodically in spite of negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cresson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>